Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.15,0:00:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a recognized authority on the 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.90,0:00:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I shall expound on the aspects of that space.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.54,0:00:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I knew of one person who lived in a 3 tatami room,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.59,0:00:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they grew more and more stubbornly set against the tides of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.78,0:00:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and last year their parents came from their hometown to pick them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.20,0:00:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a little hard to believe, but near Joudo Temple
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard there are rooms that exist with two tatami mats laid end-to-end.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.46,0:00:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you slept on them every night, there's no doubt you'd grow in height.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Kitashirakawa Baptist General Hospital's\N XXXX ward, it's said there are 1 tatami rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.96,0:00:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the students that knew of this ended up mysteriously disappearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.91,0:00:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and their friends one by one all met unfortunate fates.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.52,0:00:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then there is the 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.71,0:00:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to the 1, 2, or 3 tatami rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.06,0:00:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the 4.5 tatami room is a truly beautiful square.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it not magnificent?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.82,0:00:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2 tatamis can also form a square, but it is cramped.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.07,0:00:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, once you've made a square larger than 4.5 tatami,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.07,0:01:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it becomes as spacious as Takeda Shingen's lavatory, and one might even get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.44,0:01:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After entering university, I became a fierce supporter of the 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.33,0:01:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those people who live in 7, 8, or even 10 tatami rooms...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.54,0:01:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they truly worthy of ruling over such a space as if it is their own?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.93,0:01:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if human beings even have such capacity?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.84,0:01:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We humanity have the ability to rule 4.5 tatami and smaller spaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those reprehensible beings who greedily lust for larger area
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.22,0:01:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will surely be met by fearsome rebellion from some corner of their room.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.94,0:01:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my assertion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.73,0:01:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The 4.5 tatami room is my entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.22,0:01:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is my conviction, but now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.82,0:01:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...there is also the objective reality of the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.48,0:01:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the person responsible?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.24,0:03:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&H6C00C6&\fad(200,0)}J{\c&H000000&}-pwq
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.69,0:03:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I was a freshman university student
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.00,0:03:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and before me lay open countless doors to various different campus lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.50,0:03:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't join any of the circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.74,0:03:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A rose-colored campus life is, after all, nothing more than an illusory dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.27,0:03:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to train myself in the tranquil space known as the 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.43,0:03:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terayama Shuji once said this:\N "Throw away books and go out into the city."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what was he saying to do once you go out into the city?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the next two years I spent most of my time in the 4.5 tatami room,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and some people came to call me the "4.5 Tatami Ideologue."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.91,0:03:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HC2CBCB&\3c&H5C7178&\be1\fad(800,0)\bord1}"The 4.5 Tatami Ideologue"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.84,0:03:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my inner sanctum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Eizan train runs behind it, and though it only takes a few seconds to circle this space,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.48,0:03:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everything about me is crammed in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.75,0:04:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the north is a cheap, flimsy door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.50,0:04:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A note with venerable hints from the previous occupant is still affixed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On one side of the door is a sink of bottomless filth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.20,0:04:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,assuring the loss of any would-be cook's motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.58,0:04:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I steadfastly refuse to try my hand at cooking,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.05,0:04:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,putting into practice my belief that \N "men shouldn't set foot in the kitchen."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The majority if the north wall is a closet,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.25,0:04:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,filled carelessly with unremarkable clothing and books I never read.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My library of obscenity is also within.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In one corner of the east wall are a vacuum cleaner and rice cooker
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.62,0:04:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that do not look as if they've been heavily used,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and most of the wall is a grand library,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.88,0:04:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in which an enormous number of printed works have been assembled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.51,0:04:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the space between the southeast bookcase and my desk
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lies an area in which various junk has been thrown,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.29,0:04:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I believe if one were to venture into it alone and get lost,\N the chances of returning alive would be slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.48,0:04:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then from the south to the southwest
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there is a window which rattles as the Eizan train passes by,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.90,0:04:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there underneath it is placed my desk that has been with me through high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the west are socks in search of lost partners,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.55,0:05:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the clothes that make up my everyday life,\N and an old-fashioned world map.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A famous short story begins with a normal man that one morning turns into an insect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.03,0:06:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For me it was not something so dramatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it had definitely become a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(800,0)}"A proper man shall not be perturbed no matter what circumstances he might find himself in.\N He must think through the situation calmly."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.26,0:06:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But as I had not had much enthusiasm for going outside previously,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.33,0:06:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't going crazy trying to get out make me quite shallow as a human?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.28,0:06:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While I sat down and calmly waited it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.15,0:06:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the situation might well change for the better on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.46,0:06:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had come up with a single hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:06:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It supposed that this was a curse of that old fortune teller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.85,0:07:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was an old woman who emitted freely an eerie aura as I passed by Kiyamachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.73,0:07:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old woman said "Student there, you'll be in trouble soon!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.26,0:07:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You have made a false step in life!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.98,0:07:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I replied "That is not the case at all! I am satisfied with the way I live!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.15,0:07:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the old woman continued, "You shouldn't be so stubborn."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.94,0:07:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I can sense you have talent, so there is opportunity dangling before your eyes."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.50,0:07:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not an opportunity or anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.71,0:07:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally the old woman went "Heh, heh, heh, heh, heh..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.71,0:07:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe not, but she smiled evilly like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is anybody there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.35,0:08:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I cried out a line straight out of some crappy drama to no response,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.43,0:08:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice but to take all the embarrassment upon myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it seems we've finally entered the realm of science fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling there was once a movie
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.47,0:08:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where someone was trapped in rooms connected in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.44,0:08:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since water flows out, that means it should be connected to the outside world in some way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.75,0:08:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were some kind of mole-man and could pass through the faucet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.32,0:08:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}I could struggle through to Kyoto Water Bureau, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\c&H050505&\3c&HF3F3F3&\pos(1200,24)}"A source of protein?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an6\c&H050505&\3c&HF3F3F3&\pos(1200,448)}"Protein?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.87,0:08:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After two or so days, I ran out of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.59,0:08:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was like a Robinson Crusoe washed up on a deserted 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But for me there was a faucet with water, and furniture...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.15,0:09:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a set of everything; I could hardly call this a state of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.02,0:09:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a stroke of good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.18,0:09:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the 4.5 room next door there were fish burgers and a Castella.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.17,0:09:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, is it okay for me to eat this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.05,0:09:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really read much science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so if this really is that sort of phenomenon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would eating this Castella cause some sort of harm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.96,0:09:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if this is all some sort of hallucination, is this Castella even real?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.61,0:09:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a Castella.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.76,0:09:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Putting aside rational explanation, this was indeed an honest to goodness Castella.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.97,0:09:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so the problem of my food supply was basically solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.67,0:09:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I could not see the light of the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.37,0:09:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could not determine whether it was noon or night,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.21,0:09:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and though I made it a point to delineate each day from the next,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could not be sure that my delineations were correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.26,0:09:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't ignore the nutrients that I get from the Castella.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.52,0:09:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it a few days ago from a person named Ozu,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who came to visit a person who lives on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:09:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A couple of days before I became trapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:10:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I discovered a large cockroach outbreak in our Shimogamo Yuusuisou.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.25,0:10:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\c&H030C12&\3c&H9FB4E7&\be1\fad(100,100)}"I stopped by and went to the room on the second floor. I made a cockroach cube weapon but it malfunctioned. Sorry for the inconvenience. Please, eat this. - Ozu"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.38,0:11:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time I felt an irrational anger come over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.26,0:11:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But should I not be thankful to this Ozu person now that I am in this circumstance?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.39,0:11:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were times I despaired, but after I thought about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,perhaps this situation could be called a stroke of luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.42,0:11:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I transfer to the room next door I can get another Castella and more fish burgers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.39,0:11:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might be getting lopsided nutrition,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.97,0:11:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but food would not be a problem in the foreseeable future.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With things as they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.44,0:11:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could think of this world of 4.5 tatami rooms as a wonderful place to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From a physical perspective a 4.5 tatami space is quite small,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.70,0:11:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but one can find an expansive inner world from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.05,0:11:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Within the world of imagination there are no boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.27,0:11:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be said that I am the ultimate creator of this 4.5 tatami room!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.67,0:11:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.92,0:11:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will have fun persisting in this perfect 4.5 tatami world!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.84,0:11:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way I will show this god of fate who is boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I trembled with excitement!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.05,0:11:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs38\frz7.682\pos(419,62)\bord0\c&H151613&}"This is coffee."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.91,0:11:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that I might take this opportunity to read the books I had not read.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.14,0:11:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have as much time as I need!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.65,0:12:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fun! This is fun! This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.73,0:12:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes to pass the time I would admirably think to study,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.77,0:12:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Schrödinger's equation knocked me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.20,0:12:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a pioneer in this 4.5 tatami world, I wove a plan to bravely make my life here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would devise ways to use the Castella and fish burgers to make various other dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would undertake operation of a systematic system of growing mushrooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.15,0:12:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would even remodel many of the rooms into a bowling alley,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.96,0:12:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or movie theater, or arcade, and create all kinds of different amusement centers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.99,0:12:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would realize my own Utopia!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.28,0:12:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just thinking about it made me excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.54,0:12:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even doing something as shameful as this, no one in the world would pay any heed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.73,0:12:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not be pestered by other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.43,0:12:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is indeed a world just for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Absorbing myself in reading 20,000 Leagues Under the Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got drunk on cheap whiskey and cried out toward the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.26,0:13:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Becoming afraid of the silent world pressing down around me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.38,0:13:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sang all the songs I knew at the top of my lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so I discovered that I myself wanted to escape from this 4.5 tatami world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.92,0:13:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to admit, but I was completely and utterly sick of this 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I opened the door to the dirty hallway and headed down that dirty hallway,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.68,0:13:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there would be the dirty bathroom, and the dirty shoe boxes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.45,0:13:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then I could exit the boarding house to the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.56,0:13:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because I could always go outside when I pleased
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I confined myself to the 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.77,0:13:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most real thing to me was a single physiological need I was struggling with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.28,0:13:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To put it plainly, I couldn't stand the smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(100,0)\c&H969696&}"Lavatory"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.63,0:13:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day I couldn't stand it anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.56,0:13:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I hastily left on a journey to get far away from that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.80,0:13:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been a week since I'd been trapped in this mysterious world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.38,0:13:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's see how far these 4.5 tatami rooms go...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.15,0:14:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That day I must have traversed over 100 4.5 tatami rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.57,0:14:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and yet they still continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.87,0:14:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually I felt like a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\c&H78E6EE&\bord0}"Alchemy"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.72,0:14:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I went searching in the space between my desk
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.94,0:14:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and bookshelf known as the "Siberian Penal Colony,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found a thin little wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.40,0:14:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If each 4.5 tatami room has 1,000 yen,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.24,0:14:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,each time I move to another room I get another 1,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.37,0:14:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I move to 10 rooms, or 100 rooms, or 1,000 rooms...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made a curious discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.01,0:14:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While taking a break I thought to read\N The Curious Casebook of Inspector Hanshichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.54,0:14:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which I had bought at a used book fair,\N but it didn't exist in that 4.5 tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.79,0:14:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The collections on each bookshelf were different, if only slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.50,0:15:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed that although at a glance the 4.5 tatami rooms seemed identical,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.96,0:15:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)}they were each slightly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.50,0:15:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it was all a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.02,0:15:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why I hadn't thought to break through the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.78,0:15:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the walls are thin enough to be able to hear the conversations next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.80,0:15:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Chinese exchange student next door would often bring his girlfriend,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.13,0:15:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they'd whisper sweet nothings to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.44,0:15:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I regretted from the bottom of my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I had not studied Chinese as my second foreign language.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.94,0:15:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I broke through the wall and invaded,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.37,0:15:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he could just laugh it off with the deep tolerance of one from the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.51,0:15:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.56,0:16:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord0}"Day xxx"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.58,0:16:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that I was dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.08,0:16:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had I fallen into a so-called 4.5 tatami hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.16,0:16:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,forced to suffer for all eternity?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe... The leaves are probably turning by now on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.48,0:16:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had not eaten out for more than 1200 hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.04,0:16:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor bathed in the sun's rays, nor breathed fresh air,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.32,0:16:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor spoken with another human being!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.60,0:16:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\be1\c&H5BEFF9&\3c&H013874&}"Lucky Cat Chinese Restaurant"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.15,0:16:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this room was something I did not remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.45,0:16:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed to be the signboard for some organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the 4.5 tatami rooms have these differences?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.34,0:16:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should all be my same 4.5 tatami room, so what gave rise to these small differences?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.40,0:17:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the instant I grasped the structure of this 4.5 tatami world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.88,0:17:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bookshelves with books I had missed a chance to buy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.95,0:17:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,circles which I shouldn't have been a member of...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.65,0:17:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! These are my parallel worlds!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In these how many tens of days,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.01,0:17:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had been crossing through parallel universes of 4.5 tatami rooms
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.24,0:17:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for each of the various choices I could have made!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.90,0:17:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the dental hygienist Hanuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.02,0:17:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous autumn I'd heard rumors of a beautiful dental hygienist
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.38,0:17:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that gave the most excellent gum massages,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and so I'd visited the local dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.22,0:17:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lately I've seen a drunk Hanuki-san looking completely different
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yelling over the railing of the Mikage bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.95,0:17:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what happened to that cool professional demeanor of hers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But a mental ruffian such as myself was not able to grasp the subtlety of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.30,0:17:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what choice I made?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.56,0:18:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this world I was close to Hanuki-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.65,0:18:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lived together with a beautiful love-doll,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.11,0:18:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I even seemed to have exchanged letters with a proper lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.78,0:18:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a situation I could only dream of.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.81,0:18:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one looked like a lifestyle that had fallen into depravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.38,0:18:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost like I had become the disciple
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.94,0:18:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of that person on the second floor of the Shimogamo Yuusuisou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.20,0:18:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I threw away my backpack filled with 1,000 yen bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.84,0:18:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I would ever make use of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.50,0:18:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Funds for continuing the Proxy war?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.47,0:18:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The occupant of this room seemed like they reached toward the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.25,0:18:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remembered feeling somewhat afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.95,0:18:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I search for an even greater happiness than this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that almost like Icarus flying toward the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.54,0:18:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I recall seeing a flier about something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.46,0:18:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this that fellow I've seen at Neko Ramen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.90,0:19:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's rumored that Neko Ramen uses actual cats in its broth, but the taste is unmatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.39,0:19:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a calm conversation that reminded me of youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.93,0:19:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overheard the two worrying about who would succeed them in continuing some battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.89,0:19:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but one of them was a fine specimen of a man
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.81,0:19:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while the other was a resident of Shimogamo Yuusuisou with a face like an eggplant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.42,0:19:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I usually thought of that man as someone I did not want to associate with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.43,0:19:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to think it was that ladies' man who had such a "hobby"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.63,0:19:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For some strange reason I began to feel attached to these people I barely knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.47,0:19:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt as if I'd known them a long time, yet all that remained was this feeling of nostalgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.97,0:19:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get paid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.41,0:19:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't the cameraman hit on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.04,0:19:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not having a single person make fun of me for doing a thing like this was hard to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there were some slippery evil companion here with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.42,0:19:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.03,0:19:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there maggots crawling around your cerebral cortex?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.96,0:19:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm sure they would have completely belittled me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.12,0:20:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet every occupant of every room seemed to be having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.11,0:20:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it wasn't rose-colored,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.88,0:20:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could see each 4.5 tatami room had its own color to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.40,0:20:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it possible for me to have made these choices, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.35,0:20:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.42,0:20:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I had already realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.09,0:20:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My fate would change from even the tiniest of choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.89,0:21:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An innumerable number of I's are born,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.36,0:21:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an innumerable number of 4.5 tatami rooms are born.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.93,0:21:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, theoretically this 4.5 tatami world has no end!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.90,0:21:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it seems like these fellows can cross through the parallel worlds and gather in them one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.90,0:21:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can lose their heart with love or liven it up with raunchy stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, I only tell raunchy stories to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.62,0:21:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,always absorbed in my solitary delusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.42,0:21:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that can no longer continue.
